cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DC

This paper deals with the detection of malware in cloud infrastructure, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for this purpose involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper also involves the comparison and analysis of different CNN models, which falls under the category of machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG). The experiments are performed on a cloud testbed, which involves the study of distributed systems and cloud computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper also involves the analysis of process level performance metrics, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
